{
  "text": "The mechanisms leading to the activation of TRPM7 channels are not well understood. The C-terminal kinase has been suggested to play a role and the channels can be activated by Mg-ATP, cAMP, and a reduced PIP 2 concentration resulting from phospholipase C activity. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] However, neither the intrinsic C-terminal kinase nor phospholipase C nor phosphoinositol-3-kinase activity appear to be involved in the flow-induced enhancement of TRPM7 current. [CITATION_4] The novel findings of Oancea et al [CITATION_5] indicate that the mechanism of activation involves incorporation of new channel proteins into the plasma membrane (Figure) . Nevertheless, the mechanisms by which the smooth muscle cell senses an increase in flow and transduces it into translocation of the TRPM7 channel into the membrane remain unresolved.",
